In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or app startup) to hook into platform-specific events:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is pausing
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // runs when app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.
- On Android, `OnStop` fires when the app is no longer visible; `OnPause` fires when it loses focus.
- On iOS, `DidEnterBackground` is the equivalent background transition event.
- Use `#if` directives so platform-specific code only compiles for the target platform.
